<header id="detail-header">
	<h1>Love</h1>
</header>

	<section id="film-detail-container">
		<img src="../static/images/m15.jpeg" alt="Film poster">

		<p><em>Love</em> is a silent romantic drama film directed by Edmund Goulding and John Gilbert, starring John Gilbert and Greta Garbo.</p>

		<p>Edmund Goulding produced the film.</p>

		<p>
			It was released by Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer on November 27, 1927, with a runtime of 82 minutes.

			
				It had a budget of $487,995  and made $1.7 million at the box office.
				When adjusted for inflation in 2023, that's approximately equivalent to $8.4 million and $29.4 million, respectively.
			
		</p>

		<p>
			The film was written by Lorna Moon, Frances Marion, Marian Ainslee, and Ruth Cummings, with William H. Daniels overseeing cinematography and Hugh Wynn helping edit the film. No composer was found for the original version of the film.
		</p>

		<p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Love_(1927_US).webm">View an archived version of <em>Love</em>.</a></p>

		<p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Love_(1927_American_film)">View the Wikipedia entry for <em>Love</em>.</a></p>

		<p><a href="../index.html">Return to the list</a> to select a different film.</p>
	</section>

